            "id": "s_l2_1",
            "type": "text",
            "title": "Call Me Later 📞",
            "content": "Since async code doesn't wait, how do we know when it's done?\n\nWe pass it a **Callback Function**.\n\n\"Hey, run this function when you finish!\""
        },
        {
            "id": "s_l2_2",
            "type": "code",
            "title": "setTimeout ⏲️",
            "content": "The simplest async function is `setTimeout`.\n\nIt waits for a time (in milliseconds), then runs the callback.",
            "codeSnippet": "console.log('Start');\n\nsetTimeout(function() {\n  console.log('Wait for me!');\n}, 2000);\n\nconsole.log('End');",
            "codeLanguage": "javascript",
            "canRunCode": true
        },
        {
            "id": "s_l2_3",
            "type": "quiz",
            "title": "Quick Check 🧠",
            "content": "In the example above, what order do the logs appear?",
            "quizData": {
                "id": "q_l2_1",
                "type": "multiple_choice",
                "question": "Order of logs?",
                "options": [
                    {
                        "id": "opt1",
                        "text": "Start -> Wait for me! -> End",
                        "isCorrect": false
                    },
                    {
                        "id": "opt2",
                        "text": "Start -> End -> Wait for me!",
                        "isCorrect": true
                    }
                ],
                "explanation": "JS prints 'End' immediately because it doesn't wait for the timeout."
            }
        },
        {
            "id": "s_l2_4",
            "type": "text",
            "title": "Callback Hell 🔥",
            "content": "Callbacks can get messy if you nest them too deep.\n\nThis is called **Callback Hell** or the Pyramid of Doom."
        },
